      "content": "It's so hard to believe that surrendering could be an act of self-respect. Everyone always tells me to keep fighting, to find a reason to wake up tomorrow, but they don't understand the hollow ache in my chest. It feels less like a choice and more like an inevitability. If I were to... to finally embrace that rest you speak of, would it be seen as a tragedy, or would it finally be the quiet, graceful end I deserve?",
